<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-03T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-03T07:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/932: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-03T14:00:00+02:00">July 3, 1936—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 3—12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. In a conversation with Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs yesterday,
                            he fully confirmed statements made in Embassy’s 26, June 26, 3 p.m., as
                            to Turkish policy respecting commercial navigation of the Straits and
                            specifically authorized me so to inform you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>